### Flexible Grid Systems

#### CSS Grid for Complex Layouts
- ‚úÖ **Use CSS Grid for page-level layouts**
- ‚úÖ **Define flexible grid tracks with minmax()**
- ‚úÖ **Use auto-fit and auto-fill for responsive columns**
- ‚úÖ **Combine grid with gap for consistent spacing**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Responsive grid that adapts automatically */
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.5rem;
  padding: 1rem;
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Mobile-first grid with progressive enhancement */
.layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr; /* Mobile: single column */
  gap: 1rem;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .layout {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; /* Tablet: 2 columns */
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .layout {
    grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr; /* Desktop: sidebar + main */
    gap: 2rem;
  }
}
```

#### Flexbox for Component Layouts
- ‚úÖ **Use Flexbox for one-dimensional layouts**
- ‚úÖ **Allow items to wrap with flex-wrap**
- ‚úÖ **Use flex-grow and flex-shrink appropriately**
- ‚úÖ **Combine with gap for spacing (modern browsers)**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Flexible navigation that adapts */
.nav {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 1rem;
  align-items: center;
}

.nav-item {
  flex: 1 1 auto; /* Grow, shrink, auto basis */
  min-width: 120px; /* Prevent too-narrow items */
}

