### Responsive Typography

#### Fluid Typography
- ‚úÖ **Use clamp() for fluid font sizes**
- ‚úÖ **Scale typography with viewport units**
- ‚úÖ **Maintain readability at all sizes**
- ‚úÖ **Adjust line height with font size**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Fluid typography with clamp() */
:root {
  /* Font sizes scale smoothly between min and max */
  --font-size-xs: clamp(0.75rem, 0.7rem + 0.25vw, 0.875rem);
  --font-size-sm: clamp(0.875rem, 0.8rem + 0.375vw, 1rem);
  --font-size-base: clamp(1rem, 0.9rem + 0.5vw, 1.125rem);
  --font-size-lg: clamp(1.125rem, 1rem + 0.625vw, 1.5rem);
  --font-size-xl: clamp(1.5rem, 1.2rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);
  --font-size-2xl: clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 2.5vw, 4rem);
}

h1 {
  font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
  line-height: 1.1;
  margin-bottom: 0.5em;
}

h2 {
  font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
  line-height: 1.2;
  margin-bottom: 0.5em;
}

body {
  font-size: var(--font-size-base);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Responsive line length */
.prose {
  max-width: 65ch; /* 50-75 characters optimal */
  margin: 0 auto;
}
```

