### Content Prioritization

#### Mobile Content Strategy
- ‚úÖ **Show critical content first**
- ‚úÖ **Use progressive disclosure**
- ‚úÖ **Collapse secondary content**
- ‚úÖ **Maintain feature parity (don't hide important features)**

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Progressive disclosure with details/summary -->
<details class="expandable">
  <summary>Advanced Options</summary>
  <div class="advanced-content">
    <!-- Complex options hidden by default on mobile -->
    <label>
      <input type="checkbox" name="option1">
      Advanced option 1
    </label>
    <!-- More options... -->
  </div>
</details>

<style>
  .expandable {
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1rem;
  }
  
  summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    font-weight: 600;
    user-select: none;
  }
  
  .advanced-content {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  
  /* On desktop you may want this section expanded by default.
     Note: `open` is an HTML attribute on <details>, not a CSS property. */
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    /* If <details> is open, you can hide the summary to remove redundant chrome */
    details[open] > summary { display: none; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Optional: open by default on desktop without forcing close on mobile.
  const mq = window.matchMedia('(min-width: 1024px)');
  const details = document.querySelector('details.expandable');
  if (details && mq.matches) details.setAttribute('open', '');
</script>
```

